  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Approved. 30 vocab + 34 grammar across two structures — might / might not (25) and going to negative (9). Grants: might / mightn't (SB box modal, like should in u03). This unit drove the V-8 \"do\" glue addition (DO nothing / DO the shopping / DO your homework — \"do\" is the light pro-verb of activity phrases, not leaked content). \"mustn't\" stays out (untaught); \"gonna\" out (informal). Smoke-check fixed 2 \"do\" leaks, a \"friend\" leak, and a German term in an anagram cue. Verify round 1: fixed a broken going-to-negative carrier (missing the be auxiliary), two true-synonym vocab distractors (that's a pity / what a shame used each other), missing strict on polarity items, and reworded carriers off two name-masked words (plans → free, isn't well → is ill); round 2 added \"isn't well\" as partial translations (correct but above-level → not the model) and constrained an open verb slot. The grammar agent had proactively set strict on 10 minimal pairs (the u06 lesson carried). 5 glosses + 33 translations adjudicated; 1 benign sentence-initial-blank validator-warn. rejectRate 0.0%."
